<exercise number="32"><statement><p>Myra sells mugs at the sidewalk fair every week. Her revenue from selling <m>x</m> mugs is <m>12x-0.3x^2</m> dollars, and the cost of producing <m>x</m> mugs is <m>50+3x</m> dollars.<ol label="a">
	<li>Write an expression for the profit Myra earns from selling <m>x</m> mugs.</li>
	<li>Find Myra's profit from the sale of 10 mugs, from 15 mugs, and from 20 mugs.</li></ol></p></statement>
</exercise>

<exercise number="33"><statement><p>The owner of the Koffee Shop pours the remainder of her old house blend, which is 30% Colombian beans, into a 50-pound bin, and fills it up with her new house blend, which is 25% Colombian beans. Let <m>h</m> stand for the number of pounds of the old house blend. Write algebraic expressions to answer the questions below.
<ol label="a">
	<li>How many pounds of Colombian beans are in the old house blend?</li>
	<li>How many pounds of new blend does she pour into the bin?</li>
	<li>How many pounds of Colombian beans are in this amount of new house blend?</li>
	<li>How many pounds of Colombian beans are in the 50-pound bin?</li></ol></p></statement>
<answer><p><ol label="a">
    <li><m>0.3h</m></li>
    <li><m>50-h</m></li>
    <li><m>0.25(50-h)</m></li>
    <li><m>0.3h+0.25(50-h)</m></li></ol></p></answer></exercise>

